3. MATHEMATICAL FOUNDATIONS

3.1 Orbital Mechanics

3.1.1 Two-Body Dynamics

State vector for unit i:

```
X_i = [r_i; v_i] ∈ ℝ⁶
r̈_i = -μr_i/‖r_i‖³ + a_pert + a_control
```

Orbital parameters for circular reference orbit:

```
a = R_earth + h = 6,878 km
T = 2π√(a³/μ) = 5685 s (94.75 min)
v_circ = √(μ/a) = 7613 m/s
```

3.1.2 Perturbation Models

J₂ Oblateness:

```
a_J₂ = (3μJ₂R_earth²)/(2r⁵) × [x(5z²/r²-1), y(5z²/r²-1), z(5z²/r²-3)]
```

Secular rates for i = 45°:

```
dΩ/dt = -20.6°/day (nodal regression)
dω/dt = +10.3°/day (apsidal rotation)
```

Atmospheric Drag:

```
ρ(h) = ρ₀ exp(-h/H₀), H₀ = 8500 m, ρ₀ = 1.225 kg/m³
ρ(500 km) = 5×10⁻¹³ kg/m³
a_drag = -(1/2)ρC_DA/m × v × v ≈ 6.4×10⁻⁵ m/s²
```

Solar Radiation Pressure:

```
a_SRP = -P_☉(A/m)C_R(r_☉/‖r_☉‖) ≈ 5.5×10⁻⁵ m/s²
P_☉ = 4.56×10⁻⁶ N/m², C_R ≈ 1.2
```

3.1.3 Relative Motion (Hill-Clohessy-Wiltshire)

For unit j relative to reference orbit:

```
ẍ - 2nẏ - 3n²x = F_x/m
ÿ + 2nẋ = F_y/m
z̈ + n²z = F_z/m
```

Natural drift solution (no control):

```
y(t) = y₀ - (3/2)nx₀t  (along-track drift)
```

3.2 Electromagnetic Propagation

3.2.1 Free Space Path Loss

```
FSPL(dB) = 20log₁₀(d) + 20log₁₀(f) + 92.45
         = 167.5 dB (500 km, 5.8 GHz)
```

Received power at rectenna:

```
P_r = P_tG_tG_r(λ/(4πd))²η_atm
η_atm ≈ 0.85 (clear weather, 5.8 GHz)
```

3.2.2 Diffraction-Limited Beamforming

Minimum beam diameter:

```
D_min = 2.44λL/D_aperture
      = 2.44 × 0.0517 × 500,000 / 1000
      = 63 m (theoretical minimum)
```

For safety constraint I_max < 250 W/m²:

```
Required D_min = √(4P_total/(πI_max))
               = √(4×10⁹/(π×250))
               = 2257 m
```

Thus aperture must be limited:

```
D_aperture_max = 2.44λL/D_min
               = 2.44 × 0.0517 × 500,000 / 2257
               = 28 m
```

Sparse array with D_swarm = 1000 m satisfies safety constraint with 3.6% fill factor.

3.2.3 Phased Array Theory

Array factor for N elements:

```
AF(θ,ϕ) = Σₙ wₙ exp(j[k·rₙ·û + φₙ])
wₙ = √(Pₙ) (amplitude weighting)
k = 2π/λ (wave number)
û = [sinθcosϕ, sinθsinϕ, cosθ] (direction vector)
```

Beam steering phase shift:

```
Δφₙ = k·rₙ·(û_desired - û_broadside)
```

Grating lobe avoidance condition:

```
d/λ < 1/(1 + |sinθ_max|)
For θ_max = 0.5°: d < 1.15λ = 0.059 m
```

Since d ≈ 100 m >> 0.059 m, beam steering limited to:

```
θ_steerable ≈ λ/d = 0.000517 rad = 0.03°
```

3.3 Swarm Dynamics & Control

3.3.1 Artificial Potential Field

Total potential for unit i:

```
U_i = U_attr + Σ_{j≠i} U_rep_ij + U_obstacle
```

Attractive potential (to orbital slot):

```
U_attr = (1/2)k_attr‖r_i - r_i_desired‖²
k_attr = 1×10⁻⁶ N/m (weak attraction)
```

Repulsive potential (collision avoidance):

```
U_rep_ij = { (1/2)k_rep(1/d_ij - 1/d_safe)² if d_ij < d_safe
           { 0 otherwise
k_rep = 1×10⁶ N·m², d_safe = 50 m
```

Control force:

```
F_i = -∇U_i - k_v(v_i - v_desired)
k_v = 0.01 N·s/m (velocity damping)
```

3.3.2 Consensus-Based Phase Control

Phase dynamics (modified Kuramoto model):

```
φ̇_i = ω_i + K/N Σ_{j∈N_i} sin(φ_j - φ_i) + u_i
```

Control input for beamforming:

```
u_i = -k_p(φ_i - φ_i_desired) - k_dφ̇_i
φ_i_desired = φ_ref - (2π/λ)‖r_i - r_target‖
```

Stability proof via Lyapunov function:

```
V = (1/2)Σ_i(φ_i - φ̄)² + (1/2)Σ_i φ̇_i²
V̇ = -k_pΣ_i(φ_i - φ̄)² - k_dΣ_i φ̇_i² ≤ 0
```

3.3.3 Combined State-Space Representation

Full state for unit i:

```
x_i = [r_i; v_i; φ_i; φ̇_i] ∈ ℝ⁸
```

System dynamics:

```
ẋ_i = f(x_i) + g(x_i)u_i + Σ_j h(x_i, x_j)
```

Global stability under communication graph G:
If G is connected and λ₂(G) > 0 (algebraic connectivity), then consensus achieved exponentially:

```
‖x_i(t) - x̄(t)‖ ≤ C exp(-λ₂ t)
```

3.4 Power Systems

3.4.1 SSU Power Budget

```
SOLAR POWER:
P_solar_peak = η_pv × A_solar × S₀
             = 0.30 × 15 × 1361
             = 6125 W

Eclipse factor: 35% at 500 km
P_solar_avg = 0.65 × 6125 = 3981 W

POWER CONSUMPTION:
Transmitter (RF):   1300 W (60% efficiency)
Attitude Control:   50 W (average)
Avionics:           80 W (computer, comms)
Stationkeeping:     50 W (electrospray)
─────────────────────────────────
Total:              1480 W

POWER MARGIN:
P_net = 3981 - 1480 = 2501 W surplus
Margin = 2501/1480 = 69% ✅
```

3.4.2 Thermal Management

Heat generated:

```
Q_gen = P_solar × (1 - η_pv) + P_elec × (1 - η_elec)
      = 6125 × 0.70 + 1480 × 0.40
      = 4288 + 592 = 4880 W
```

Radiative cooling at 300 K:

```
Q_rad = εσA_rad T⁴
      = 0.85 × 5.67×10⁻⁸ × 30 × 300⁴
      = 1170 W (insufficient)
```

Active cooling required:

```
A_radiator = Q_gen/(εσT⁴)
           = 4880/(0.85×5.67×10⁻⁸×300⁴)
           = 12.5 m²
```

3.4.3 End-to-End Efficiency

```
η_total = η_pv × η_power × η_RF × η_transmission × η_rectenna
        = 0.30 × 0.95 × 0.60 × 0.85 × 0.85
        = 0.124 = 12.4%
```

For 1M units at 4.1 kW each:

```
P_delivered = 4.1 GW × 0.124 × 0.65 (sunlight)
            = 330 MW (conservative)
```

