6. HARDWARE IMPLEMENTATION

6.1 SSU Detailed Design

6.1.1 Structural Design

```
MATERIALS:
Primary Structure: Carbon fiber reinforced polymer (CFRP)
Solar Array Substrate: Kapton polyimide (25 μm)
Deployment Mechanism: Shape memory alloy (SMA) actuators
Mass Breakdown:
- Structure: 2.0 kg (15%)
- Solar Arrays: 4.0 kg (31%)
- Power System: 3.0 kg (23%)
- RF System: 2.0 kg (15%)
- Propulsion: 1.0 kg (8%)
- Avionics: 1.0 kg (8%)
TOTAL: 13.0 kg
```

6.1.2 Power System

```
SOLAR ARRAYS:
Type: Triple-junction GaAs
Efficiency: 30% (BOL), 27% (EOL)
Area: 15 m² (5 m × 3 m deployed)
Mass: 2.5 kg (0.17 kg/m²)
Specific Power: 2450 W/kg (peak)

BATTERY SYSTEM:
Chemistry: Lithium-ion (LFP)
Capacity: 500 Wh (2.5 kg)
Depth of Discharge: 80%
Cycle Life: 5000 cycles
Operating Temperature: -20°C to +40°C

POWER MANAGEMENT:
MPPT Efficiency: 98%
Bus Voltage: 28 V ±10%
Distribution: 5V, 12V, 28V rails
Fault Protection: Current limiting, over-voltage protection
```

6.1.3 RF Transmission System

```
TRANSMITTER CHAIN:
Oscillator: 5.8 GHz DRO (Dielectric Resonator Oscillator)
Phase Shifter: MEMS digital, 6-bit (5.6° resolution)
Amplifier: GaN HEMT, 60% efficiency
Filter: 5.8 GHz ±50 MHz bandpass
Antenna: 10 dBi patch array (0.3 m × 0.3 m)

PERFORMANCE SPECIFICATIONS:
Output Power: 1300 W average
Frequency Stability: ±10 ppm
Phase Accuracy: ±0.5° RMS
Spectral Purity: -60 dBc harmonics
Spurious Emissions: -70 dBc
```

6.1.4 Propulsion System

```
TYPE: Electrospray (colloidal)
Propellant: EMI-BF4 ionic liquid
Thrust: 0.1-1.0 mN (adjustable)
Specific Impulse: 1500 s
Total ΔV: 50 m/s
Mass: 0.8 kg (dry), 0.2 kg (propellant)
Power: 50 W average
Lifetime: 10,000 hours
```

6.1.5 Avionics Suite

```
PROCESSOR: 
- Main: ARM Cortex-M7 @ 400 MHz (FreeRTOS)
- Redundant: ARM Cortex-M4 @ 200 MHz

MEMORY:
- Flash: 2 GB (radiation-tolerant)
- RAM: 512 MB (EDAC protected)

SENSORS:
- Star Tracker: ±1 arcmin accuracy
- IMU: MEMS, 0.01°/s resolution
- GPS Receiver: L1/L2, <1 m accuracy
- Magnetometer: 3-axis, ±8 Gauss range

COMMUNICATIONS:
- S-band: 2.4 GHz, 1 Mbps (TT&C)
- ISL: 60 GHz, 100 Mbps (neighbor comms)
- Optical: 1550 nm laser (backup ranging)
```

6.2 Ground Station Design

6.2.1 Rectenna Array

```
DESIGN: Dual-polarization dipole with Schottky diodes
AREA: 10 km² (3.16 km × 3.16 km)
ELEMENT SPACING: λ/2 = 0.02585 m
NUMBER OF ELEMENTS: 1.5×10¹⁰
CONVERSION EFFICIENCY: 85% (DC output)
OUTPUT VOLTAGE: 10 kV DC
GRID CONNECTION: HVDC to AC inverter station

SAFETY FEATURES:
- Perimeter fence with RF monitoring
- Automatic shutdown if humans detected
- Redundant safety interlocks
- Emergency dephasing transmitter
```

6.2.2 Control Center

```
ARCHITECTURE: Redundant server cluster
COMPUTING: 1000 CPU cores, 10 TB RAM
STORAGE: 1 PB RAID array
NETWORK: 100 Gbps fiber optic
DISPLAY: 10×4K video wall
REDUNDANCY: N+2 power, cooling, networking

SOFTWARE STACK:
- Orbit Determination: Extended Kalman Filter
- Swarm Control: Distributed MPC
- Fault Management: Expert system
- User Interface: Web-based dashboard
```

