```
DEPLOYMENT SEQUENCE:
1. Release from Starship (tumbling)
2. Solar array deployment (SMA activation)
3. Attitude acquisition (magnetorquers)
4. Communication establishment (S-band)
5. Navigation initialization (GPS + star tracker)
6. Swarm integration (ISL network formation)
7. Beamforming test (low power)

CHECKOUT DURATION: 24 hours per unit
SUCCESS CRITERIA: 99.9% units operational
```

