9. RISK ASSESSMENT & MITIGATION

9.1 Technical Risks

9.1.1 High-Risk Items

```
RISK 1: Phase Synchronization Failure
Probability: 30% (initial), 5% (mature)
Impact: Catastrophic (no power delivery)
Mitigation:
- Redundant reference satellites
- Multiple pilot signal frequencies
- Graceful degradation algorithms
- Ground-based phase correction

RISK 2: Swarm Collision Cascade
Probability: 10% (initial), 1% (mature)
Impact: Catastrophic (system loss)
Mitigation:
- Conservative safe distances (50 m)
- Redundant collision avoidance sensors
- Emergency dispersal protocols
- Insurance coverage

RISK 3: Power System Degradation
Probability: 40% (10-year lifetime)
Impact: Major (reduced output)
Mitigation:
- 20% power margin
- Online replacement strategy
- Radiation-hardened components
- Predictive maintenance algorithms
```

9.1.2 Medium-Risk Items

```
RISK 4: Communications Latency
Probability: 20%
Impact: Moderate (reduced efficiency)
Mitigation: Predictive control, local autonomy

RISK 5: Thermal Management Failure
Probability: 15%
Impact: Moderate (unit failure)
Mitigation: Redundant radiators, heat pipes

RISK 6: Deployment Mechanism Failure
Probability: 10%
Impact: Moderate (partial loss)
Mitigation: Multiple deployment methods
```

9.2 Economic Risks

9.2.1 Market Risks

```
RISK: Electricity Price Decline
Scenario: Solar+battery costs drop to $0.03/kWh
Probability: 20%
Impact: High (reduced competitiveness)
Mitigation: Focus on markets with high storage needs

RISK: Launch Cost Increases
Scenario: Starship costs remain at $100M/launch
Probability: 30%
Impact: High (doubled LCOE)
Mitigation: Alternative launch providers, larger units
```

9.2.2 Financial Risks

```
RISK: Capital Cost Overrun
Scenario: Actual costs 50% above estimates
Probability: 40%
Impact: High (reduced ROI)
Mitigation: Phased deployment, contingency budget

RISK: Financing Delay
Scenario: 2-year delay in Series B funding
Probability: 25%
Impact: Moderate (schedule slip)
Mitigation: Government grants, strategic partners
```

9.3 Political Risks

9.3.1 Regulatory Risks

```
RISK: Frequency Allocation Denial
Probability: 10%
Impact: Catastrophic (no operation)
Mitigation: Alternative frequencies, international lobbying

RISK: Export Control Restrictions
Probability: 15%
Impact: High (limited deployment)
